## CSS Class Naming

- Use kebab-case for CSS classes: `.overview-stat-box`
- Component-based naming: `.component-element-modifier`
- State classes: `.active`, `.selected`, `.disabled`

## Layout Patterns

### Grid Systems
```css
/* 3-column layout for overview cards */
.overview-stats {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 20px;
}

/* Table-style grids */
.user-cumulative-table {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 2fr 3fr 1fr 1fr 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 15px;
}
```

### Flexbox Patterns
```css
/* Navigation items */
.menu-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 12px 20px;
}

/* Button groups */
.chart-controls {
    display: flex;
    gap: 8px;
    align-items: center;
}
```

## Interactive Elements

### Hover States
```css
.interactive-element:hover {
    background-color: #3a3a3a;
    color: #fff;
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
}
```

### Active States
```css
.element.active {
    background-color: #4a9eff;
    color: white;
}
```

## Component Standards

### Buttons
**MUST MATCH** existing button styles - DO NOT CREATE NEW BUTTON STYLES:

- Primary: `.analytics-btn` (blue background: #4a9eff)
- Secondary: `.chart-btn` (gray background: #3a3a3a)
- Export: `.export-btn` (full width, icon + text)

**When creating new buttons, always use existing button classes or match their exact styling.**

### Forms
**MUST MATCH** existing form styles - DO NOT CREATE NEW FORM STYLES:

- Inputs: `.search-box` (dark theme: #2a2a2a background, #e1e1e1 text)
- Selects: `.setting-select` (consistent styling: #3a3a3a background)
- Toggle switches: `.toggle-switch` (custom implementation)

**When creating new form elements, always use existing form classes or match their exact styling.**

### Cards
**MUST MATCH** existing card styles - DO NOT CREATE NEW CARD STYLES:

- Statistics: `.overview-stat-box` (hover effects, clickable, #2a2a2a background)
- Content: `.settings-section` (accordion style, #2a2a2a background)
- Tables: `.user-cumulative-info` (grid-based, #2a2a2a background)

**When creating new cards, always use existing card classes or match their exact styling.**